\date{2025-01-17}
\p{A morita morphism [(in #{\mathbf{Top}} or #{\mathbf{Mfd_\R}})](todo) between two [groupoid objects](fp-000Q) 
is a [morphism of groupoids](fp-000S) #{f : X_\bullet \rightarrow Y_\bullet} such that}

\ul{
    \li{#{f_0 : X_0 \rightarrow Y_0} is a surjective submersion, i.e. admits local sections}
    \li{
        The following diagram is [cartesian](empty)
        \texfig{
            \begin{tikzcd}
                {X_1} & {X_0\times X_0} \\
                {Y_1} & {Y_0 \times Y_0}
                \arrow["{s,t}", from=1-1, to=1-2]
                \arrow["{f_1}"', from=1-1, to=2-1]
                \arrow["\lrcorner"{anchor=center, pos=0.125}, draw=none, from=1-1, to=2-2]
                \arrow["{f_0 \times f_0}", from=1-2, to=2-2]
                \arrow["{s,t}"', from=2-1, to=2-2]
            \end{tikzcd}
        }
    }
}

\p{
    Here the diagram being cartesian [translates into](todo) #{f} being fully faithful (consider maps from a point.) And the requirement on #{f_0} is a bit stronger than #{f} being [essentially surjective](todo).
}